# Coffer Commons License (CCL)

Copyright © 2025  
All rights reserved.

---

## Purpose

Coffer is a system designed to make honesty and trust a shared commons.

This license exists to ensure that the Coffer system, its guarantees,
and its meaning are never privatized, enclosed, or sold.

Coffer is not a product.
It is a commons.

---

## Grant of Permission

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person or organization
obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation (the “System”),
to use, study, modify, and redistribute the System,
provided that all conditions of this license are met.

This permission is automatically revoked upon violation.

---

## Non-Commercialization of the System (Absolute)

The System MUST NOT be monetized, in whole or in part.

This includes, but is not limited to:

- selling the System, in original or modified form,
- selling access to the System or System-mediated functionality,
- gating features, commands, or interactions behind payment,
- selling in-game advantages, currency, priority, or exclusivity
  derived from the System,
- incorporating the System into commercial products or services,
- monetizing trust, evaluation outcomes, or guarantees provided by the System.

Coffer may exist on monetized servers.
Coffer itself may not be monetized.

If access to Coffer, its functionality, or its outcomes
is a reason money is requested,
this license is violated.

---

## Derivative Works

Derivative works, including adapters, forks, extensions, or modifications
based on or interacting with Coffer Core,
MUST be distributed under this license
and MUST NOT be sold or commercially licensed.

No derivative work may introduce monetization,
access gating, or paid advantage tied to Coffer.

Free redistribution and modification are permitted.
Commercial enclosure is not.

---

## Law and Integrity Requirement

Any use, modification, or distribution of the System
MUST comply with the Coffer Law, Charter, and governing documentation.

Specifically:

- Truth must not be approximated, inferred, or guessed.
- Refusal must be preferred over dishonesty.
- Core authority must not be bypassed or reinterpreted.
- Denials must not be suppressed, reframed, or hidden.
- Mutation must remain evaluation-last.

Dishonest use constitutes a license violation.

